                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9275.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Simpich</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-23T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 23, 1913, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department is informed that Francisco Villa is holding seven Englishmen, forty
                    Frenchmen, several Spaniards and Italians and about forty Germans as “hostages
                    against an attack by the Federal forces.”</p>
                <p>Bring to attention of General Carranza and say that in view of authority which he
                    is reported to exercise over revolutionary leaders, it is hoped he will desire
                    to order that all foreigners in Torreon be given immediately absolute liberty to
                    depart from Torreon at will and that ample protection be afforded. Report action
                    Carranza takes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
